main event: An object with starlike characteristics was detected moving rapidly overhead on 5 October 1962.
interesting points: The object appeared on radar indicating it was high in the atmosphere., The sighting was reported by the USS Lansing (DER 388)., The initial bearing of the object was between 205-215 degrees., The distance from the observer was estimated to be 30-40 miles., Various conclusions were drawn suggesting it could have been a balloon, aircraft, or satellite based on insufficient data.
